                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12651376" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 27 Nov 2008 16:02:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The other problem is we never set QueryParser.setEnablePositionIncrements(true)&lt;br/&gt;
This means that the indexed version will have gaps but the phrase query produced will not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can see the problem with this query on the example data:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/select?q=features:%22Optimized%20High%20Volume%20Web%20Traffic%22&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/select?q=features:%22Optimized%20High%20Volume%20Web%20Traffic%22&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12651378" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 27 Nov 2008 16:06:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that changes the default for the parser and fixes the example config.&lt;br/&gt;
We may need to fix other example configs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Q: is this really the default we want in the example config?&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Optimized &amp;lt;stopword&amp;gt; High Volume Web Traffic&quot; will match&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Optimized High Volume Web Traffic&quot; will not match.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12651724" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sat, 29 Nov 2008 16:38:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775588" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:51:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
